original_problem:
Suppose that $x$ is an integer that satisfies the following congruences: \begin{align*}
3+x &\equiv 2^2 \pmod{3^3} \\
5+x &\equiv 3^2 \pmod{5^3} \\
7+x &\equiv 5^2 \pmod{7^3}
\end{align*}What is the remainder when $x$ is divided by $105$?

original_solution:
A number is congruent to the sum of its digits $\pmod 9$. Thus, \begin{align*}
1+22+333&+4444+55555+666666+7777777+88888888\\ &\equiv 1+4+9+16+25+36+49+64 \\
&\equiv 1+4+0+7+7+0+4+1 \\
&= 24 \\
&\equiv \boxed{6}\pmod 9.
\end{align*}
